      • clipPolygonSutherlandHodgman

        public static Vector2D[] clipPolygonSutherlandHodgman​(Vector2D[] clipRegionCCW,
                                                      Vector2D[] polyToClip,
                                                      double dupeRadius)
        Clips a polygon using the Sutherlan-Hodgman algorithm. This algorithm favors speed over accuracy, so there are some cases this algorithm is not suited for (For example, if clipping a concave polygon would result in multiple output polygons).
        Parameters:
        clipRegionCCW - The clip region. MUST be convex. MUST have counter-clockwise vertex order.
        polyToClip - The polygon to clip.
        dupeRadius - If multiple consecutive points in the output polygon are within this distance of eachother, consider them to be duplicates and remove the extra ones. Set to <= 0 to skip this check
        Returns:
        The clipped polygon
